description:
TypeScript reports: `Property 'title' does not exist on type 'never'`

**Location:** `app/routes/posts.$slug.tsx:16`

**Issue:**
The MetaFunction type inference fails because the loader returns data without proper type annotation. TypeScript infers `never` because it doesn't recognize the Post return type.

**Fix:**
Add explicit return type to the loader:
```typescript
export const loader: LoaderFunction = async ({ params }): Promise<Post> => {
  invariant(params.slug, "expected params.slug");
  return getPost(params.slug);
};
```

Or use typed useLoaderData:
```typescript
const post = useLoaderData<Post>();
```
